Counseille as y haue seide biforn . And knowen well that ye may ꝑper/parforme youre 

Emprise ; Conferme it sadly than . till it be at an ende ;

Nowe is it reason and 

tyme that y shewe you whan and wherfore that ye mowe change youre Counseillours 

withoute reprof ;

and tell me ; 

howe . likith you . or what semeth you . by oure counsaillours . That we haue 

chosen in oure psent nede .

where as in 

so grete . and in so high anede . it had ben necessarie mo counseillours and more delibaciou 

to ꝓproforme youre emprise ;

and of  

the veniaunce takyng vppon that wolde engendre a nother veniaunce and mochill 

sorowe and wastyng of Richesse as y seide ;

And 

Salamon seith that he that entremetith hym of noyse or strif of a nother man ; Is like 

to hym that taketh an hounde by the eeres ;

And it is 

writen that he is worthy to lese his privilage . that mys vseth the myght and the 

powere that is yeve hym ;
